    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "99166f96_0145b8d7",
        "filename": "util/stream/log_file_processor.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-16T22:19:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"Processor\" is already used conventionally to refer to stackwalking or other dump analysis that we\u0027re not doing here and I think it\u0027d be better to avoid overloading that name.\n\nOther possible names:\n- LogFileEncoder\n- FileEncoder (since there\u0027s no requirement that we\u0027re actually operating on log files here).\n- StreamPipeline. I expect you\u0027re going to have other similar classes for differently constructed pipelines (e.g. something that will output to a LogOutputStream). I suspect this class can be abstracted to handle all of them. WDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 25,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "21041827db6cf8685468a266654af31028b33337",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2fbc7638_d293052f",
        "filename": "util/stream/log_file_processor.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000825
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-17T06:48:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Chose FileEncoder.\n\nThe minidump will be written to logcat like below, no new class needed.\n\n      StringFile minidump_string_file;\n      minidump.WriteEverything(\u0026minidump_string_file);\n      ZlibOutputStream z_stream(ZlibOutputStream::Mode::kCompress,\n                                std::make_unique\u003cBase94OutputStream\u003e(Base94OutputStream::Mode::kEncode, std::make_unique\u003cLogOutputStream\u003e()));\n\n      z_stream.Write(reinterpret_cast\u003cconst uint8_t *\u003e(minidump_string_file.string().data()),\n                     minidump_string_file.string().size());\n      z_stream.Flush();",
      "parentUuid": "99166f96_0145b8d7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 25,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "21041827db6cf8685468a266654af31028b33337",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
